Subject: in_dxf: block members need entmode 0 (explicit owner), not 3

A regular block's BlockBegin/members/ENDBLK were imported with entmode 3
(0b11 = model space, no owner in the handle stream). Conformant readers
(AutoCAD/BricsCAD/ODA) therefore resolve the BlockBegin owner to
*Model_Space and report "AcDbBlockTableRecord(H): BlockBegin owner Id is
invalid (<mspace handle>)", then auto-recover. AutoCAD/ODA write these as
entmode 0 (explicit owner = the block record). Model space (entmode 2) and
paper space (entmode 1) were already correct.

Set regular block members to entmode 0 so the explicit owner (already held
in ent->ownerhandle from DXF group 330) is written. On the COFOPRI cadastre
the "owner invalid" warnings drop 10 -> 0; on casa bueno 45 -> 0; both still
open and render identically in BricsCAD. Model-space entities keep entmode 2
(verified: 929 mspace LINEs stay 2, 1385 block-member LINEs become 0, exactly
matching ODA's ACAD2000 output). The entmode==3 uses in encode.c are all in
encode_preR13_entities (r11 section routing), so r2000+ is unaffected. 254
unit tests green.

Co-authored-by: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

--- a/src/in_dxf.c
+++ b/src/in_dxf.c
@@ -13864,7 +13864,11 @@
                   else
-                    entmode = ent->entmode = 3; // regular block entities
+                    // Regular block members use entmode 0 (explicit owner =
+                    // block record), matching AutoCAD/ODA. entmode 3 (model
+                    // space) makes conformant readers resolve the BlockBegin
+                    // owner to *Model_Space -> "BlockBegin owner Id invalid".
+                    entmode = ent->entmode = 0; // regular block entities
